The information provided in the documents supports that Rio Tinto Group is involved in producing titanium dioxide. Specifically, document 12 mentions that "the plant in southwestern Quebec produces steel, scandium and titanium dioxide," and document 60 states, "The plant in southwestern Quebec currently produces steel, scandium and titanium dioxide." This confirms that Rio Tinto Group does produce titanium dioxide as part of its operations.
